    "body": "## Problem\n\nWhen running MXFP4 models with the TRITON backend and expert parallelism (EP) enabled (e.g. `vllm serve openai/gpt-oss-20b -tp=2 -ep`), the server crashes with an illegal memory access.\n\n`triton_kernel_moe_forward` passes `expert_map` through to `triton_kernel_fused_experts` but never actually applies it. As a result, `legacy_routing` produces routing data using **global** expert IDs that don't correspond to the **local** weight indices on each EP rank.\n\n## Fix\n\nWhen `expert_map` is provided, bypass `legacy_routing` and split routing into three explicit steps, matching the approach already used by `OAITritonExperts.apply()`:\n\n1. Perform top-k selection from gating logits (yields global expert IDs)\n2. Remap global → local expert IDs via `expert_map`\n3. Build routing data structures from the local IDs using `make_routing_data`\n\nThe non-EP path (`expert_map is None`) is unchanged and continues to use `legacy_routing`.\n\n## Why not set `is_monolithic=False`?\n\nAn earlier attempt disabled the monolithic path for TRITON+EP, intending to route through the modular kernel path. This doesn't work because:\n- MXFP4 does not implement `maybe_make_prepare_finalize`, so the modular kernel wrapper is never created\n- The `apply()` method only supports CUTLASS/MARLIN backends — calling it with TRITON hits an assertion error\n\nFixing the remapping directly in `triton_kernel_moe_forward` keeps `is_monolithic=True` for TRITON and avoids both issues.\n\n\n<!-- markdownlint-disable -->\n\n## Purpose\nFix https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/issues/34259\n\n## Test Plan\nAdded unit tests verifying:\n- `is_monolithic` remains `True` for TRITON regardless of EP size\n- The correct routing path (top-k + `make_routing_data` vs `legacy_routing`) is exercised based on whether `expert_map` is present\n\n## Test Result\n\n---\n<details>\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\n\n- [ ] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\n- [ ] The test plan, such as providing test command.\n- [ ] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\n- [ ] (Optional) Release notes update. If your change is user facing, please update the release notes draft in the [Google Doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YyVqrgX4gHTtrstbq8oWUImOyPCKSGnJ7xtTpmXzlRs/edit?tab=t.0).\n</details>\n\n",
